## Roadmap: Phase 3 (Real Sky Data & Location)

### Task 10: astronomy-engine Integration
**Goal:** Replace the hardcoded Sun stub with real celestial calculations.
- **File:** `src/astronomy/skyModel.ts`
- [ ] Compute Sun position using `astronomy-engine` `SunPosition` / `Equator` + `Horizon`.
- [ ] Compute Moon position using `GeoMoon` + `Horizon`.
- [ ] Compute visible planets: Mercury, Venus, Mars, Jupiter, Saturn using `GeoVector` + `Horizon`.
- [ ] Include bright named stars (Sirius, Canopus, Arcturus, Vega, Capella, Rigel, Procyon, Achernar, Betelgeuse, Hadar) using `StarPosition` or fixed ICRS coords + `Horizon`.
- [ ] Filter bodies with `altitude < -18┬░` (astronomical twilight cutoff) before returning.
- [ ] Assign correct magnitudes to all bodies.
- [ ] All existing tests continue to pass; add unit tests for each body type.

### Task 11: Location Cache & IP Geolocation
**Goal:** Complete the location resolution pipeline per spec ┬ž4.
- **Files:** `src/location/resolveLocation.ts`, `src/location/cacheLocation.ts`
- [ ] Implement `cacheLocation.ts`: read/write lat+lon to a JSON file in `~/.astrolink/cache.json`.
- [ ] Implement IP geolocation via `https://ipapi.co/json/` (no API key required, free tier).
- [ ] Wire priority: CLI Ôćĺ cache Ôćĺ geo Ôćĺ fallback in `resolveLocation.ts`.
- [ ] On successful geo lookup, write result to cache.
- [ ] On geo failure, show footer warning "Location fallback: Sydney".
- [ ] Respect `--no-geo` flag (skip IP lookup entirely).
- [ ] Unit tests for each priority branch.

### Task 12: Unicode Safety & Min Terminal Guard
**Goal:** Graceful degradation for hostile environments.
- **Files:** `src/render/asciiGrid.ts`, `src/App.tsx`
- [ ] Detect Unicode support: check `process.env.LANG` / `process.env.TERM` for UTF-8, or probe stdout with a test write.
- [ ] If Unicode unavailable, fall back: `ÔśëÔćĺO`, `ÔŚÉÔćĺo`, symbols stay `* + .`.
- [ ] In `App.tsx`, if `dimensions.width < 80 || dimensions.height < 24`, render a single warning line instead of the sky view.
- [ ] Warning clears automatically when terminal is resized back to minimum.
- [ ] Tests for ASCII fallback symbol mapping and small-terminal guard.

---

## Phase 3 Testing Strategy
- **Unit Tests:** skyModel bodies (Sun, Moon, each planet, sample stars), location priority branches, ASCII fallback map.
- **Integration Tests:** Full location resolution chain (mock fetch), terminal resize below minimum.
- **Validation:** Visual spot-check against a known planetarium (Stellarium) for Ôëą3 bodies at a known time/location.
